-- Japanese Bought Net 764.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-03-13T23:52:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/japanese-bought-net-764-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 8 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 764.4 billion yen ($8.0 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 269.6 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 48.3 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 446.4 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 838.2 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 1121.9 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1886.2 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 2170
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
